            "content": "Tile Roofs:\n- Under 20 years old: Repair almost always makes sense unless catastrophic storm damage\n- 20-35 years old: Evaluate based on extent of damage, underlayment condition, and frequency of repairs\n- Over 35 years old: Replacement usually better long-term value unless tiles in exceptional condition\n- 40+ years old: Seriously consider replacement—underlayment certainly needs attention even if tiles look okay\n\nShingle Roofs:\n- Under 12 years old: Repair unless extensive damage, may have warranty coverage\n- 12-18 years old: Decision depends on damage extent and how many years until planned replacement\n- 18-22 years old: Lean toward replacement if repair exceeds $3,000-4,000\n- Over 22 years: Replacement recommended—additional repairs are temporary solutions\n\nMetal Roofs:\n- Under 25 years old: Repair unless structural damage or coating system failure\n- 25-40 years old: Evaluate based on maintenance history and panel/fastener condition\n- Over 40 years: Consider replacement if significant rust or multiple fastener failures"
